(1986, 'GTag', '', 'Renewables Paragraph', '', 'This 3 625 MW is broadly in accordance with the capacity allocated to renewable energy generation in the IRP 2010-2030.  This REIPPP was designed so as to contribute towards socio-economic and environmentally sustainable growth, and to start and stimulate the renewable industry in South Africa.<br />\nThe REIPP procurement programme has had two Bid Submission Phases to date, with the Third Bid Submission Phase commencing in August 2013<br />\nIn terms of this REIPPP, the Bidders are required to bid on tariff and the identified socio-economic development objectives of the Department.  The tariff will be payable by the Buyer pursuant to the PPA to be entered into between the Buyer and the Project Company of a Preferred Bidder.  Each Facility procured in terms of the REIPPP will be required to achieve commercial operation by not later than the dates set out in the RFP for the REIPPP.<br />\nBased upon the principles of the REIPPP, the Department in the near future intends to advertise a separate ‘Small Projects IPP Procurement Programme’ for electricity generation projects of less than 5MW.  The determination for this electricity generation capacity was made by the Minister together with that of the REIPPP.<br />\nOn 19 December 2012 the Minister of Energy issued three further determinations for electricity generation by IPPs, the first of which was for an additional 3200 MW of energy to be procured from renewable energy sources.  This new determination to add electricity generation capacity to the existing REIPPP, bringing the total available for procurement under that programme to 6925 MW.', 'a:1:{s:3:"tag";s:1:"p";}', 'file_manager', '', '*', '2013-06-12', '2013-06-18', 97, 1929),
(1987, 'GTag', '', 'Renewables Paragraph', '', 'Medium Term Risk Mitigation and Baseload IPP procurement programmes\nThe other two determinations dealt with medium term risk mitigation energy and baseload energy, and in terms of these the Minister determined that the following new generation capacity is needed to contribute towards energy security:', 'a:1:{s:3:"tag";s:1:"p";}', 'file_manager', '', '*', '2013-06-12', '2013-06-18', 98, 1929),
(1988, 'GTag', '', 'Renewables List', '', 'Medium Term Risk Mitigation Energy\n<br /><ul><li>800 MW, to be generated from Industrial Cogeneration energy sources (which may include amongst others, one or more of the following: biomass; industrial wastes and Combined Heat and Power), which represents part of the Cogeneration supply side options identified in Table 1 of Annexure E of the IRP 2010-2030 for reducing the medium term supply-demand shortfall which was assessed at that point to be approximately 9 terawatt hours or 1000 MW as referred to in paragraph 2 on page 62 of Annexure E of the IRP 2010-2030; and</li>\n<li>474 MW to be generated from Natural Gas, which represents the capacity allocated to “Gas CCGT (natural gas)”, under the heading "New build", for the years 2019 to 2020, in Table 3 of the IRP 2010-2030;\nBaseload Energy</li>\n<li>2500 MW to be generated from Coal, which is in accordance with the capacity allocated to “Coal (PF, FBC, Imports)”, under the heading "New build", for the years 2014 to 2024, in Table 3 of the IRP 2010-2030;</li>\n<li>2652 MW (baseload or mid merit) to be generated from Natural Gas (which includes Liquefied Natural Gas or Natural Gas delivered by pipeline from a Natural Gas Field), which represents the capacity allocated to “Gas CCGT (natural gas)” and “OCGT (diesel)”, under the heading "New build", for the years 2021 to 2025, in Table 3 of the IRP 2010-2030; and</li>\n<li>2609 MW to be generated from Hydro energy sources, which represents the capacity allocated to “Imported Hydro” under the heading "New build", for the years 2022 to 2024, in Table 3 of the IRP 2010-2030.</li>\n</ul>', 'a:1:{s:3:"tag";s:3:"div";}', 'file_manager', '', '*', '2013-06-12', '2013-06-18', 99, 1929),
(1989, 'GTag', '', 'Renewables Paragraph', '', '<strong>Future IPP procurement programmes</strong><br />\nAny future procurement programmes to procure electricity capacity from IPPs will be subject to any determination that the Minister may make.  In making any such determination the Minister will be guided by the IRP 2010-2030.<br />\nPursuant to such determination, the Department will design appropriate procurement programmes for the procurement of this electrical capacity.  The Department is committed to ensuring that such procurement programmes comply with the requirements of, amongst other things, the Constitution of the Republic of South Africa and the Public Finance Management Act.<br />\nIn designing any future procurement programmes, the Department will have regard to the determinations, which state that the electrical capacity should be procured through one or more IPP procurement programmes as contemplated in the Electricity Regulations on New Generation Capacity.', 'a:1:{s:3:"tag";s:1:"p";}', 'file_manager', '', '*', '2013-06-12', '2013-06-18', 100, 1929),
