(1986, 'GTag', '', 'List Item', '', '<ol><li>Once the project proponent has activated its access to the website, it will see two tabs on the top of the website, the first is the <b>Download RFRI</b>  and the second is the <b>RFRI Response Form.</b><br /></li><li>The project proponent must download the PDF version of the RFRI document after accessing the relevant link under the <b>Download RFRI</b> tab. <br /></li><li>The project proponent must first read the RFRI and then start to complete the RFRI Response Form(s) on the website. If the project proponent wants to view the RFRI Response form before completing it, the project proponent must initially complete Section 1 of the RFRI Response form, save it, select the print option and print the RFRI Response form.  </li><li>The RFRI Response forms can be completed in sections, be saved numerous times and printed. When the project proponent is finally happy that no more changes need to be made to the RFRI Response Form (s) they must be submitted. <br /></li><li>Once the RFRI Response Form is submitted it cannot be retracted and no changes can be made to the document. The printed RFRI Response forms together with any attachments must be submitted as the <b>"hard copy"</b> referred to in the RFRI. <br /></li></ol><br /><br />', 'a:1:{s:3:"tag";s:3:"div";}', 'file_manager', '', '*', '2013-06-12', '2013-06-13', 0, 1929),
